{
  "stem": "7832.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think if they-- even if they find out that we are friends, they-- they going to keep us for this, whatever is coming up.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she was telling me her-- how she got in there and-- and she had nobody.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- she was all alone too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was like my strength, helping me to cope with not having my family and not having my friends and not having my cousins and not having anybody that looks familiar.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she says, this is how I'm dealing with-- with the situation.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you have to-- I'll never forget, she said, you have to be very strong.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You have to close your eyes when you see somebody suffering and just say, he's really not suffering.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You have to go on with your taking care of yourself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You cannot stop and feeling sorry for anybody, because feeling sorry is not making it better for the person, but it's making it worse for you.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was trying to explain to a 12, 13-year-old how to live under these circumstances.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I listened to her, but it-- it just didn't make sense.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then finally, we got to the fourth experiment-- the third experiment, which was they selected the five of us and they-- they-- again, with the smooth skin-- and they said that we're going to another camp, but we will be back.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they said that we will go.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So she found out from the girl in charge that they're taking us to Majdanek.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and she says, well, what is Majdanek?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she said, well, I hate to tell you this, but I think that Ilse Koch, that was taking the-- the human skin and making gloves and lampshades in, I think, her-- in the camp she was doing that was Innsbruck.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
